<subSubSection id="0FFE8C837B7E0F994A5BDE1EB5A9F9AC" lastPageId="121" lastPageNumber="122" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="9BEF4ADAEF14A68300C65383BA11DB4E" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C4628A8656C6F55AB02CFF4B732C8BD9" lastPageId="121" lastPageNumber="122" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">
Externally there is little to distinguish this species from 
<taxonomicName id="B7AAEF600E4919CB28470158D725177E" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Baconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Baconia guartela" order="Coleoptera" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guartela">Baconia guartela</taxonomicName>
(see Figs 32
<normalizedToken id="14F2DA3B13BA998EBAE2BC7238FE26F9" originalValue="D–F">D-F</normalizedToken>
), with a transverse, crenulate mesometaventral stria, relatively impunctate 
<pageBreakToken id="91AF2E7D4305A061730E49A2A1F3DF23" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" start="start">frons</pageBreakToken>
and pronotum, and somewhat longer elytral striae than typical for the group. However, the male 8th sternite has the apices somewhat broadly rounded, with conspicuous apical setae, the 9th tergite has very short, broad basal apodemes and apical lobes, also with several conspicuous apical setae, the spiculum gastrale is subtriangular, with small, ventrally directed, apicolateral processes. The aedeagus shows very pronounced dorsoventral curvature, but not the strong deflection of the basal piece seen in 
<taxonomicName id="38C2C2BCABA3FF583D39E0145A39511D" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Baconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Baconia guartela" order="Coleoptera" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guartela">Baconia guartela</taxonomicName>
. The specimen from Peru, a male, shows some slight genitalic differences, and is therefore excluded from the type series.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4F1E272E6B81A07BB60218BE8C997F78" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="CE25B44B0722671B1B167152C27A20D8" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="20467D028E8EDF1B65BD14FDF947C8F1" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">
